(fifthQuint)Hib-MenCY-TT Vaccine Study Compared to Licensed Hib and Meningococcal Serogroup C Conjugate Vaccines.

 The study will be conducted in 2 stages: a 3-dose primary vaccination at 2, 4 and 6 months of age and a booster vaccination at 12 to 15 months of age.

 All subjects will have 3 blood samples taken.

 Half of the subjects of each group will have a blood sample taken just prior to the administration of the third dose of the primary vaccination and the other half of the subjects of each group will have a blood sample taken at one month after the third vaccine dose of the primary vaccination phase.

 In addition, all subjects of all groups will have a blood sample taken before and 42 days after administration of the booster dose.

